lie after lie, some of which Hitler seems even to have come to believe
himself. The lies are often minor. Little white fibs. It is as if Hitler
had come to be so used to lying, that he could not even describe minor
incidents of his childhood without distorting them. Little men tell little
lies. But little men can do terrible evils.
<p>
